entry.title: Foreign Nationals Start to Leave Gaza at Egyptian Border
entry.content: More than 400 people, including wounded Palestinians and some Americans, crossed into Egypt from the Rafah border, Egyptian and U.S. officials say.

entry.title: In West Bank, Israeli Settlers Step Up Attacks Against Palestinians
entry.content: A series of shootings that left six dead and two communities divided is part of a spasm of violence.

entry.title: Italy's Rumbling Supervolcano Has Half a Million Residents on Edge
entry.content: Campi Flegrei, not far from ill-fated Pompeii, has had 2,500 earthquakes in the past three months, a sign of volcanic activity deep underground.
